Exact Requirement
•	10 minute window 
o	At ≥500 requests → warning email
o	At ≥700 requests → block for 1h + block email
•	Hourly window 
o	At ≥1000 requests → warning email
o	At ≥2000 requests → block for 8h + block email
•	Daily window 
o	At ≥15000 requests → warning email
o	At ≥20000 requests → block for 24h + block email
•	Auto activation happens after 1h / 8h / 24h respectively, with an “account re enabled” email.
•	Precedence ensures if hourly and 10 min thresholds are both exceeded at the same check, the 8 hour block is applied (and similar for daily).
•	No double counting in a cluster: each node reads only its access log segment and maintains its own file offset; counters are centralized in plugin settings (DB backed).
